Plus Markets Unveils Details of Interest-Rate Swap Contract

-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 
2011-05-19T06:00:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/plus-markets-unveils-details-of-interest-rate-swap-contract.html
Plus Markets Group Plc (PMK) , which runs
the smallest U.K. stock exchange, unveiled details of an
interest-rate swap contract as the company works toward opening
its derivatives exchange by the end of next month.  The Swap Index Contract will be cleared by LCH.Clearnet
Group Ltd., the London-based exchange said in a statement today.  “Today’s announcement is an important step on the road to
the delivery of the Plus Derivatives Exchange, which we expect
to launch by the end of June,” Chief Executive Officer Cyril Theret said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Rummer in London at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
